%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20all%20factors%20in%20why%20middle%20managers%20are%20finding%20their%20jobs%20are%20most%20at%20risk%20during%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20critics%20think%20the%20repercussions%20of%20a%20flatter%20corporate%20structure%20could%20be%20less%20mentorship%20and%20feeling%20more%20stress%20coming%20from%20above%2C%20according%20to%20hiring%20experts%2C%20there%20are%20also%20benefits.%20And%20one%20might%20be%20that%20Zoomers%20get%20better%20at%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESophie%20O'Brien%2C%20a%20Gen%20Z%20hiring%20expert%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20recruitment%20agency%20Pollen%20Careers%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20role%20of%20a%20middle%20manager%20is%20to%20effectively%20%26quot%3Bmicro-manage%20juniors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20actually%2C%20there's%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20this%20is%20not%20productive%20and%20limits%20people's%20learning%20potential%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20effective%20team%20development%20is%20when%20people%20are%20given%20autonomy%20and%20the%20freedom%20to%20fail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Brien%20said%20fresh%20talent%20is%20often%20better%20equipped%20to%20identify%20issues%20with%20traditional%20ways%20of%20working%20in%20a%20company%2C%20which%20could%20help%20with%20shaking%20up%20the%20structure%20to%20be%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20not%20having%20a%20micromanager%20picking%20apart%20their%20work%20could%20benefit%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20don't%20feel%20they%20need%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bspoon-fed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Brien%20said%20micromanagers%20can%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bdetrimental%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20Zoomers'%20productivity%2C%20especially%20if%20it's%20their%20first%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20cause%20them%20to%20feel%20demotivated%2C%20doubt%20or%20second-guess%20themself%2C%20and%20make%20them%20disengage%20from%20their%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20if%20their%20ideas%20or%20work%20is%20constantly%20being%20rehashed%20or%20rejected%2C%20they'll%20naturally%20lose%20interest%20in%20their%20role.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20having%20multiple%20layers%20of%20management%20will%20give%20Zoomers%20%26quot%3Bmore%20autonomy%20and%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20this%20can%20encourage%20empowerment%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20for%20them%20to%20take%20full%20responsibility%20for%20their%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224704711-2e44-4a1a-8ca7-cdb658a343db%5C%22%3EDoing%20it%20right%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20are%20skeptical%20of%20companies%20axing%20middle%20managers%20say%20it%20could%20mean%20junior%20staff%20won't%20receive%20the%20mentorship%20needed%20to%20climb%20the%20ladder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20issues%20should%20only%20arise%20with%20this%20shift%20if%20companies%20don't%20handle%20it%20properly%2C%20O'Brien%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20ensure%20young%20hires%20feel%20supported%20is%20to%20introduce%20mentoring%20programs%2C%20she%20said%2C%20because%20this%20will%20give%20them%20first-hand%20exposure%20to%20people%20from%20different%20teams%20with%20different%20levels%20of%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20should%20also%20be%20introduced%20to%20the%20leadership%20team%2C%20O'Brien%20added%2C%20so%20they%20have%20visibility%20within%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20not%20only%20benefits%20more%20junior%20employees%20but%20mentors%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20now%20in%20a%20working%20world%20where%20there%20can%20be%20four%20generations%20working%20together%2C%20and%20the%20intergenerational%20divide%20has%20never%20been%20so%20vast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20room%20for%20more%20conversations%20between%20people%20at%20all%20levels%20%26quot%3Bcan%20make%20for%20greater%20empathy%2C%20understanding%2C%20and%20better%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReverse%20mentoring%20can%20also%20help%20bring%20an%20organization%20together%2C%20O'Brien%20said%2C%20to%20help%20give%20junior%20employees%20access%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20senior%20staff%20and%20leaders%2C%20so%20they%20are%20not%20stuck%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrible%20boss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20it's%20about%20%26quot%3Btrial%20and%20error%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Brien%20said%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20brave%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20just%20making%20a%20change%20and%20adopting%20a%20growth%20mindset%20as%20a%20business%20can%20create%20positive%20change%2C%20even%20if%20it%20fails%2C%20because%20it%20shows%20you%20want%20to%20do%20the%20best%20by%20people%2C%20that%20you%20won't%20just%20stick%20to%20the%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af8c36d3-2d2e-40bc-a6a6-183c4d1cc43d%5C%22%3E'Unbossing'%20can%20impact%20anyone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-won-great-resignation-now-losing-the-big-firing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20are%20currently%20most%20likely%20in%20the%20firing%20line%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20great%20unbossing%20can%20come%20to%20anyone.%20So%2C%20it%20may%20be%20a%20wake-up%20call%20for%20those%20who%20are%20coasting%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-quiet-quitting-work-ethic-millennials-money-struggles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20simply%20in%20the%20wrong%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Rymsha%2C%20a%20visiting%20lecturer%20in%20management%20at%20The%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20Lowell%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20cutting%20middle%20managers%20%26quot%3Balleviates%20the%20time%20and%20costs%20of%20upskilling%20and%20developing%20them%20into%20effective%20leaders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20cutting%20managers%20to%20%26quot%3Bweed