C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20scams%20are%20only%20becoming%20more%20prevalent%2C%20and%20with%20new%20AI%20technology%2C%20Harvard%20researchers%20say%20they%20could%20become%20much%20more%20difficult%20to%20avoid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fieeexplore.ieee.org%2Fdocument%2F10466545%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%2060%25%20of%20participants%20were%20duped%20by%20AI-automated%20phishing%20emails%2C%20which%20was%20comparable%20to%20the%20success%20rates%20of%20phishing%20messages%20created%20by%20humans%2C%20they%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2024%2F05%2Fai-will-increase-the-quantity-and-quality-of-phishing-scams%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%20Business%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-phishing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhishing%20scams%3C%2Fa%3E%20trick%20users%20into%20sharing%20personal%20information.%20A%20scammer%20will%20usually%20send%20an%20email%20or%20some%20other%20message%20pretending%20to%20be%20a%20company%20or%20individual%20asking%20for%20credit%20card%20information%2C%20passwords%2C%20or%20other%20sensitive%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20phishing%20scams%20are%20nearly%20as%20old%20as%20the%20internet%2C%20AI%20models%20are%20enhancing%20%26quot%3Btheir%20severity%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20said.%20In%20the%20study%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20large%20language%20models%20can%20automate%20the%20%26quot%3Bentire%20phishing%20process%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20from%20crafting%20the%20emails%2C%20identifying%20targets%2C%20and%20collecting%20information%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20carrying%20them%20out%20by%2095%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20this%2C%20we%20expect%20phishing%20to%20increase%20drastically%20in%20quality%20and%20quantity%20over%20the%20coming%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20AI%20models%20could%20make%20phishing%20scams%20worse%2C%20the%20researchers%20suggest%20they%20could%20also%20be%20used%20to%20help%20detect%20and%20fight%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20AI%20models%20are%20better%20at%20it%20than%20others.%20Claude%20correctly%20identified%20phishing%20attempts%20even%20in%20%26quot%3Bnon-obvious%20phishing%20emails%2C%20sometimes%20outperforming%20human%20detection%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20AI%20models%20tested%20in%20the%20study%20also%20provided%20%26quot%3Bexcellent%20recommendations%26quot%3B%20for%20responding%20to%20phishing%20emails%20once%20they%20correctly%20identified%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20during%20our%20experiment%2C%20LLMs%20encouraged%20users%20who%20received%20an%20attractive%20discount%20offer%20email%20to%20verify%20the%20offer%20with%20the%20company's%20official%20website%2C%20which%20is%20a%20great%20strategy%20to%20avoid%20phishing%20attacks%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20says%20the%20best%20way%20to%20avoid%20phishing%20scams%20is%20to%20never%20click%20on%20a%20link%20from%20someone%20you%20don't%20know%20in%20an%20email%20or%20text%20message.%20The%20agency%20says%20to%20check%20if%20you%20have%20an%20account%20with%20the%20company%20or%20know%20the%20person%20and%20if%20you%20don't%2C%20report%20the%20message%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumer.ftc.gov%2Farticles%2Fhow-recognize-and-avoid-phishing-scams%23report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnti%20Phishing%20Working%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-phishing-scams-automation-detection-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C