20out%20emails%2C%20disregarding%20any%20damage%20I've%20caused%20to%20conversational%20flow.%20I%20never%20slow%20down%20long%20enough%20to%20consider%20how%20little%20I'm%20giving%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-new-friends-as-an-adult-arranged-friendships-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20friendships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20how%20uncomfortable%20it%20must%20be%20to%20sit%20with%20someone%20so%20checked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaying%20on%20top%20of%20my%20work%20is%20my%20top%20priority%3B%20doing%20so%20makes%20me%20feel%20responsible%20and%20important%2C%20a%20sensation%20I%20relish.%20I'm%20no%20longer%20the%20messy%20unreliable%20fuckup%20I%20felt%20like%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20I%20think%2C%20but%20a%20sturdier%20person%3B%20respectable%2C%20established%2C%20moored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20only%20a%20distracted%20friend.%20Outside%20childcare%20duties%2C%20I'm%20barely%20present%20at%20home.%20After%20the%20baby's%20bath%20and%20bedtime%20routines%2C%20when%20Alex%20and%20I%20finally%20sit%20down%20to%20eat%20takeout%2C%20I%20often%20spend%20the%20meal%20refreshing%20my%20inbox%20rather%20than%20asking%20about%20his%20day.%20Later%2C%20I%20pull%20out%20my%20laptop%20and%20check%20traffic%20numbers%20while%20we're%20supposed%20to%20be%20watching%20%26quot%3BGame%20of%20Thrones.%26quot%3B%20Instead%20of%20reaching%20for%20him%20in%20bed%2C%20I%20lie%20awake%20with%20my%20back%20turned%2C%20proactively%20identifying%20and%20solving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-work-boss-left-office-on-stretcher-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproblems%20at%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20head.%20Priding%20myself%20on%20my%20diligence%2C%20how%20little%20escapes%20my%20gaze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20capitalist%20society%2C%20onerous%20work%20is%20often%20as%20satisfying%20as%20it%20is%20depleting.%20We've%20been%20conditioned%20from%20a%20young%20age%20to%20find%20pleasure%20in%20accomplishment's%20rigors%20and%20strains.%20It%20feels%20natural%20to%20view%20my%20overwork%20as%20noble%2C%20to%20settle%20into%20that%20foundational%20groove%20of%20the%20brain.%20In%20these%20first%20high-achieving%20months%2C%20I%20revel%20in%20the%20rush%20of%20my%20own%20competence%2C%20but%20the%20accompanying%20stress%20means%20it's%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20health%20of%20my%20central%20nervous%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThreats%20to%20my%20job%20real%20and%20imagined%20keep%20my%20amygdala%20firing%20throughout%20my%20days.%20Goals%20at%20the%20company%20I%20work%20for%20remain%20in%20flux%3B%20it's%20hard%20to%20predict%20which%20way%20to%20march.%20I%20survive%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20and%20I'm%20assured%20my%20department%20is%20not%20a%20future%20target%2C%20but%20my%20position%20never%20feels%20quite%20safe.%20The%20job%20provides%20my%20family's%20healthcare%20and%20our%20livelihood.%20By%20definition%2C%20I'm%20dependent%20on%20it.%20Keeping%20me%20motivated%20to%20work%20harder%2C%20to%20do%20as%20much%20as%20I%20can%20with%20less%2C%20is%20an%20institutional%20feature%20not%20a%20bug.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.simonandschuster.com%2Fbooks%2FAmbition-Monster%2FJennifer-Romolini%2F9781668056585%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmbition%20Monster%3A%20A%20Memoir%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20by%20Jennifer%20Romolini.%20Copyright%202024%20Jennifer%20Romolini.%20Published%20by%20Atria%20Books.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdream-job-cost-relationships-suffered-ambition-monster-excerpt-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717409221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665609c4239fda2da6cc1a84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdream-job-cost-relationships-suffere