ption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20Express%20used%20to%20be%20your%20dad's%20card.%20OK%2C%20your%20rich%20dad's%20card.%20Or%2C%20fine%2C%20your%20rich%20friend's%20rich%20dad's%20card.%20But%20now%2C%20for%20a%20growing%20cohort%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%2C%20it's%20their%20card%2C%20too.%20Amex%20has%20cracked%20the%20code%20with%20the%20youngs%2C%20and%20it's%20managed%20to%20do%20so%20without%20giving%20up%20its%20prestige%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-are-amex-offers-available-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Express%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20been%20viewed%20as%20%3Cem%3Ethe%3C%2Fem%3E%20fancy%20credit-card%20company.%20Its%20products%20were%20historically%20seen%20as%20being%20for%20jet-setters%20and%20the%20wealthy%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bwealthy%26quot%3B%20usually%20translating%20to%20%26quot%3Bolder.%26quot%3B%20The%20idea%20wasn't%20that%20young%20people%20wouldn't%20use%20any%20Amex%20products%20but%20that%20they'd%20get%20initiated%20into%20the%20low-level%20ones%20and%20then%20eventually%20graduate%20to%20the%20most%20premium%20versions%20of%20its%20cards%20as%20they%20got%20better%20jobs%2C%20made%20more%20money%2C%20etc.%20Amex%20also%20wasn't%20broadly%20accepted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fits-time-to-break-up-with-american-express-2015-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecause%20of%20its%20swipe%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20what%20merchants%20pay%20every%20time%20they%20run%20a%20credit%20card.%20For%20years%2C%20customers%20were%20a%20lot%20likelier%20to%20get%20a%20no%20on%20using%20their%20Amex%20at%20any%20given%20merchant%20than%20they%20were%20when%20paying%20with%20a%20Mastercard%20or%20Visa%2C%20sometimes%20making%20the%20former%20a%20headache%20to%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20has%20started%20to%20shift.%20Amex%20has%20updated%20its%20benefits%20mix%20to%20focus%20on%20younger%20people%20with%20the%20things%20they%20might%20like.%20It%20has%20used%20those%20perks%20to%20get%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20that%20%26quot%3Bwealthy%26quot%3B%20status%20%E2%80%94%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20premium%20cards%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%20The%20companies'%20acceptance%20rate%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwsj-reports-amex-paying-merchants-accept-credit-cards-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20also%20much%20improved%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20enter%20a%20restaurant%20or%20store%20checking%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20American%20Express%20sticker%20is%20on%20the%20door.%20Add%20all%20this%20up%2C%20and%20Amex%20morphs%20into%20a%20popular%2C%20relatively%20accessible%20status%20symbol%20for%20young%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fruits%20of%20the%20new%20strategy%20were%20pretty%20clear%20in%20the%20company's%20first-quarter%20earnings%20presentation%3A%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20consumers%20made%20up%2033%25%20of%20its%20billed%20business%20in%20its%20consumer%20division%2C%20basically%20meaning%20using%20its%20products%20for%20purchases.%20By%20contrast%2C%20Gen%20X%20represented%2037%25%2C%20and%20baby%20boomers%2031%25.%20According%20to%20the%20company%2C%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20consumers%20made%20up%2060%25%20of%20its%20new%20customer%20acquisitions%20worldwide%2C%20and%2075%25%20of%20its%20new%20platinum%20and%20gold%20accounts%20were%20opened%20by%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20members.%20Those%20accounts%20come%20with%20some%20nice%20rewards%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20high%20accompanying%20fees.%20The%20gold%20card%20costs%20%24250%20a%20year%2C%20and%20the%20platinum%20%24700.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20realized%20that%20going%20after%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20was%20a%20key%20thing%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Amex%20CEO%20Steve%20Squeri%20said%20in%20an%20April%20interview%20with%20Jim%20Cramer%20on%20CNBC.%20He%20explained%20that%20while%20the%20company%20used%20to%20target%20them%20with%20no-fee%20cards%2C%20it%20had%20now%20turned%20to%20trying%20to%20attract%20them%20with%20premium%2C%20high-fee%20cards.%20%26quot%3BWith%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zs%2C%20what%20we%20realized%20is%20that%20they%20wanted%20access%2C%20they%20wanted%20experiences%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20get%20special%20privileges%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20So%20Amex%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmex%20has%20implemented%20a%20number%20of%20tactics%20to%20pull%20off%20its%20youth%20revolution%20and%20cement%20its%20place%20as%20a%20status%20symbol%20among%20relatively%20affluent%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20consumers.%20For%20one%20thing%2C%20as%20Squeri%20alluded%20to%2C%20it's%20done%20some%20thinking%20about%20what%20the%20younger%20crowd%20wants%20in%20terms%20of%20rewards.%20Yes%2C%20travel%20points%20for%20flights%20and%20hotels%20are%20nice%2C%20but%20so%20are%20other%20benefits%20that%20have%20helped%20turn%20it%20into%20more%20of%20a%20lifestyle%20card%20than%20just%20a%20travel%20card%2C%20Michael%20Miller%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Morningstar%20Research%2C%20said.%20The%20company%20has%20folded%20in%20rewards%20such%20as%20credits%20on%20Uber%20rides%2C%20Disney%20streaming%20services%2C%20and%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20subscriptions.%20It%20puts%20money%20toward%20Saks%20shopping%20sprees%20and%20offers%20credits%20for%20Walmart%2B%20memberships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20they%20finance%20this%20is%20they%20work%20with%20the%20actual%20retailers%20to%20split%20the%20cost%2C%20and%20they%20essentially%20act%20as%20really%20high-end%20coupons%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20really%20how%20they%20keep%20the%20appeal%20and%20keep%20it%20luxury%2C%20by%20not%20really%20compromising%20on%20the%20price%20of%20the%20cards%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmex%20gives%20some%20of%20its%20customers%20special%20access%20for%20various%20events%2C%20including%20a%20chance%20to%20buy%20tickets%20early%20or%20get%20certain%20passes%20to%20the%20US%20Open%20and%20Coachella.%20And%20it%20sometimes%20gives%20them%20reserved%20spaces%20inside%20those%20events%2C%20too%2C%20keeping%20its%20reputation%20of%20exclusivity%20intact.%20I%2C%20for%20one%2C%20have%20found%20myself%20at%20events%20staring%20at%20some%20American%20Express%20exclusive%20space%20and%20trying%20to%20see%20whether%20anyone%20I'm%20with%20has%20the%20magic%20card%20to%20get%20us%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmex%20is%20like%2C%20'You%20know%20what%3F%20We%20know%20that%20this%20age%20cohort%20is%20attending%20Coachella.%20We're%20going%20to%20have%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20have%20a%20platinum%20card%2C%20you%20can%20get%20into%20the%20Amex%20tent.%20And%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20simple%20things%20that%20are%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20or%20expensive%20to%20access%20at%20Coachella%2C%20free%20water%20fountains%2C%20a%20place%20to%20kind%20of%20sit%20in%20air%20conditioning%2C'%26quot%3B%20Daisy%20Hernandez%2C%20the%20credit-cards%20editor%20at%20The%20Points%20Guy%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20people%20who%20are%20like%2C%20'I'm%20going%20to%20have%20this%20credit%20card%20because%20I%20want%20this%20extra%20premium%20access.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20hungry%20for%20experience%20over%20possessions%2C%20are%20not%20sleeping%20on%20the%20Amex%20travel%20perks%2C%20either.%20The%20platinum%20card%2C%20for%20example%2C%20offers%20credits%20on%20hotels%20and%20airline%20fees%2C%20covers%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20Clear%20Plus%20membership%20for%20airport%20security%2C%20and%20grants%20complimentary%20lounge%20access%20at%20multiple%20airports.%20It%20also%20has%20restaurant-reservation%20perks%20through%20the%20platform%20Resy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20haven't%20ditched%20the%20travel%20stuff%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20more%20of%20an%20addition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20young%20consumers%2C%20having%20an%20Amex%20rewards%20card%20is%20sort%20of%20like%20having%20a%20good%2C%20varied%20subscription%20service%20that%20runs%20them%20less%20than%20%2460%20a%20month.%20Amex%20says%20that%20the%20platinum%20card's%20credits%20are%20worth%20something%20like%20%241%2C500%20a%20year%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20double%20the%20annual%20fee.%20(Amex%2C%20of%20course%2C%20has%20a%20ton%20of%20cards%20that%20aren't%20premium%20and%20have%20a%20variety%20of%20different%20perks%20or%20benefits.%20It's%20a%20real%20choose-your-own-adventure%20situation%20depending%20on%20which%20one%20you%20might%20want%2C%20if%20you%20do%20at%20all.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20American%20Express'%20part%2C%20this%20all%20makes%20sense.%20Many%20young%20consumers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintelligence%2Fthe-death-of-cash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20carry%20cash%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20expect%20to%20be%20able%20to%20put%20everything%20on%20their%20cards.%20The%20company's%20continued%20focus%20on%20high-income%2C%20high-spending%20customers%2C%20including%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%2C%20gives%20it%20more%20bargaining%20power%20with%20merchants%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20turn%20those%20consumers%20away.%20And%20once%20Amex%20gets%20those%20customers%20in%20the%20pipeline%2C%20it%20has%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20to%20get%20value%20out%20of%20them%20compared%20with%20older%20consumers%20who%20are%20closer%20to%20retirement%20and%2C%20you%20know%2C%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20next%20generation%2C%20and%20they%20feel%20they%20have%20a%20great%20offering%20and%20great%20growth%20potential%20because%20if%20you've%20only%20catered%20to%20the%20much%20older%2C%20those%20folks%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20around%2C%20potentially%2C%20in%2020%20years%2C%20whereas%20the%20millennial%20still%20will%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephen%20Biggar%2C%20the%20director%20of%20financial-institutions%20research%20at%20Argus%20Research%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmex%20isn't%20alone%20in%20targeting%20the%20rich%2C%20young%20crowd.%20Chase%20Sapphire%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fchase-sapphire-reserve-vs-amex-platinum-card%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiving%20it%20a%20run%20for%20its%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20some%20of%20its%20offerings%2C%20namely%2C%20its%20Reserve%20card.%20And%20all%20consumers%20might%20want%20to%20consider%20the%20trade-offs%20of%20their%20pricey%20rewards%20cards.%20Research%20has%20found%20that%20rewards%20cards%20can%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonfed.org%2Fpublications%2Fresearch-department-working-paper%2F2020%2Fdistributional-effects-payment-card-pricing-merchant-cost-pass-through-united-states-canada.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransfer%20of%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20poor%20to%20the%20rich%20because%20of%20the%20high%20swipe%20fees%20that%20come%20with%20them%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fvisa-mastercard-swipe-fees-premium-credit-cards-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethough%20those%20swipe%20fees%20are%20coming%20down%20a%20little%20for%20a%20few%20years%3C%2Fa%3E).%20And%20even%20if%20you're%20not%20concerned%20about%20what%20happens%20to%20the%20guy%20paying%20cash%20behind%20you%20at%20the%20bodega%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20pay%20off%20your%20credit-card%20bill%20every%20month%20and%20instead%20carry%20a%20balance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fthe-goods%2F2023%2F1%2F17%2F23550612%2Fcredit-card-rewards-fico-score-balance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyou%20may%20not%20get%20the%20bang%20for%20your%20buck%20on%20your%20rewards%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20that%20a