usinessinsider.com%2Fyann-lecun-meta-ai-chief-elon-musk-feud-intensifies-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20incredible%20oblivion%20of%20Judge%20Marvin%20Isgur%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20Judge%20Marvin%20Isgur%2C%20and%20Judge%20David%20Jones%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6659e62c1cd3b17790421091%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221191%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDominic%20Bugatto%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20mild%20Houston%20day%20in%20March%202021%2C%20Judge%20Marvin%20Isgur%20prepared%20to%20oversee%20the%20only%20case%20on%20his%20docket%20that%20morning.%20It%20was%20a%20motion%20to%20recuse%20his%20longtime%20colleague%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20David%20Jones%2C%20from%20a%20case%20involving%20a%20bankrupt%20engineering%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMotions%20are%20the%20bread%20and%20butter%20of%20the%20US%20court%20system%2C%20and%20litigants%20use%20recusal%20motions%20to%20request%20a%20new%20judge%20if%20they%20have%20concerns%20about%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest%20or%20bias.%20An%20independent%20judge%20hears%20the%20arguments%20and%20decides%20if%20there%20is%20enough%20evidence%20to%20grant%20the%20motion%2C%20requiring%20the%20assigned%20judge%20to%20step%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20day%2C%20the%20circumstances%20were%20anything%20but%20usual.%20The%20motion%2C%20filed%20months%20earlier%2C%20had%20just%20been%20updated%20with%20a%20shocking%20allegation%3A%20Jones%20was%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bromantic%20relationship%26quot%3B%20with%20attorney%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20his%20former%20clerk%20and%20then%20a%20lawyer%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20a%20Texas%20firm%20that%20often%20appeared%20before%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court%2C%20where%20the%20pair%20of%20judges%20handled%20the%20most%20high-profile%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Van%20Deelen%2C%20the%20plaintiff%20in%20a%20shareholder%20case%20against%20executives%20of%20the%20engineering%20company%20McDermott%20International%2C%20wrote%20that%20he'd%20received%20a%20document%20in%20the%20mail%20alleging%20the%20relationship.%20The%20note%20went%20further%2C%20saying%20that%20Freeman%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bstrategic%20link%26quot%3B%20between%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorneys%2C%20including%20Matthew%20Cavenaugh%2C%20and%20cases%20handled%20by%20Jones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20and%20Cavenaugh%20were%20both%20well%20known%20to%20Isgur.%20Freeman%20had%20clerked%20for%20Jones%20for%20six%20years%2C%20and%20later%20joined%20a%20special%20committee%20the%20two%20judges%20created%20as%20they%20centralized%20large%20bankruptcy%20cases%20under%20their%20control.%20Cavenaugh%20was%20a%20former%20Isgur%20clerk.%20And%20yet%20Isgur%20had%20chosen%20himself%20when%20Jones%20asked%20him%20to%20assign%20a%20judge%20to%20decide%20the%20recusal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20choice%20wasn't%20all%20that%20surprising%20given%20their%2030-year%20relationship.%20As%20law%20partners%2C%20Isgur%20and%20Jones%20had%20formed%20a%20lifelong%20bond%2C%20and%20as%20bankruptcy%20judges%2C%20they%20had%20created%20an%20ambitious%2C%20if%20controversial%2C%20machine%20for%20attracting%20cases%20to%20the%20Southern%20District.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20special%20and%20close%20relationship%20that%20came%20from%20being%20a%20mentor%20to%20a%20best%20friend%20to%20a%20colleague%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Houston%20bar%20said%20at%20a%20December%202023%20hearing%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20created%20something%20very%20big%20and%20special%20in%20this%20district.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20motion%20filed%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court%20in%20March%202021%20says%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Blive-in%20girlfriend%26quot%3B%20of%20Judge%20David%20Jones.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665d18d9cc442a2f676d0a4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22296%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20excerpt%20from%20an%20October%202023%20lawsuit%20that%20would%20set%20off%20a%20crisis%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20Van%20Deelen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20Deelen's%20motion%20threatened%20to%20unravel%20it%20all%2C%20exposing%20grave%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20and%20a%20tight%20network%20of%20informal%20communications%20that%20allowed%20lawyers%2C%20including%20Freeman%2C%20to%20leverage%20their%20access%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20cases%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ebuilding%20their%20firm's%20clout%20and%20revenue%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%26quot%3BJudge%20Jones's%20secret%20relationship%20with%20Ms.%20Freeman%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20US%20Trustee%20wrote%20in%20a%20November%20filing%2C%20%26quot%3Bcreated%20an%20unlevel%20'playing%20field'%20for%20every%20party%20in%20interest%20in%20every%20case%20Jackson%20Walker%20had%20before%20Judge%20Jones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Houston%20attorneys%20said%20they%20considered%20Isgur%20a%20brilliant%20judge%20whose%20response%20to%20the%20recusal%20motion%20was%20out%20of%20character.%20Over%20nearly%2020%20years%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20during%20which%20he%20had%20overseen%20thousands%20of%20cases%2C%20he%20developed%20a%20history%20for%20being%20a%20stickler%20on%20questions%20of%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.courthousenews.com%2Ftrustee-rightly-removed-for-billing-big-easy-trip%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissued%20an%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20removing%20an%20attorney%20who'd%20worked%20at%20his%20former%20firm%2C%20W.%20Steve%20Smith%2C%20from%20his%20duties%20overseeing%20a%20bankruptcy%20estate%20after%20Smith%20had%20sought%20reimbursement%20from%20the%20estate%20for%20around%20%243%2C500%20for%20a%20three-day%20personal%20stay%20prior%20to%20an%20oral%20argument%20in%20New%20Orleans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Isgur%20joined%20another%20judge%20to%20initiate%20an%20investigation%20into%20another%20trustee%20for%20what%20they%20considered%20improprieties%20surrounding%20a%20creditor%20payment%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20a%20former%20chief%20judge%20had%20described%20the%20approach%20as%20a%20longstanding%20practice.%20In%20at%20least%20two%20other%20cases%2C%20Isgur%20has%20personally%20questioned%20witnesses%20he%20called%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20including%2C%20once%2C%20Jones%2C%20while%20he%20was%20appearing%20before%20Isgur%20as%20an%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankruptcy%20judges%20have%20broad%20discretion%2C%20what%20the%20author%20Michael%20Lewis%20has%20called%20%26quot%3Bsensational%20powers%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20decide%20what%20evidence%20to%20allow%20in%20a%20case.%20And%20yet%20in%20the%20Jones%20recusal%20case%2C%20the%20aggressive%20Isgur%20was%20nowhere%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20he%20ordered%20the%20motion%20and%20the%20anonymously%20authored%20document%20sealed.%20Then%2C%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20roughly%2040-minute%20long%20hearing%2C%20he%20refused%20to%20admit%20the%20anonymous%20note%20into%20evidence.%20He%20did%20not%20call%20to%20the%20stand%20either%20Freeman%20or%20Cavenaugh%2C%20though%20he%20knew%20them%20both%20well.%20And%20when%20Van%20Deelen%20asked%20for%20time%20to%20depose%20witnesses%20about%20the%20allegations%2C%20Isgur%20shut%20that%20down%2C%20his%20tone%20giving%20off%20a%20sense%20of%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20your%20motion%20for%20a%20continuance%20is%20denied%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20audio%20of%20the%20judge's%20remarks.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20let%20you%20take%20a%20deposition%20about%20the%20contents%20of%20an%20anonymous%20letter.%20That%20would%20be%20totally%20outrageous.%26quot%3B%20Minutes%20later%2C%20Isgur%20denied%20the%20motion%20for%20recusal.%20A%20US%20district%20court%20judge%20later%20denied%20Van%20Deelen's%20appeal%2C%20agreeing%20that%20the%20note%20had%20no%20evidentiary%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20may%20have%20been%20largely%20forgotten%2C%20one%20of%20any%20number%20of%20denials%20handed%20down%20every%20day%20throughout%20the%20United%20States%20court%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20anonymous%20note%20resurfaced%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20later%20when%20Van%20Deelen%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20Jones%2C%20alleging%20retaliation%2C%20this%20time%20relying%20on%20evidence%20that%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20owned%20a%20home%20together%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20to%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cspan%3E(Jones%20has%20filed%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20in%20that%20case%2C%20which%20remains%20pending.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%2010%20days%2C%20Jones%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fbankruptcy-judge-jones-named-in-a-lawsuit-over-romantic-relationship-with-local-lawyer-71df2c00%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadmitted%20he%20and%20Freeman%20were%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20earned%20a%20rare%20public%20rebuke%20from%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%2C%20and%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20as%20if%20a%20meteor%20had%20hit%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fbankruptcy-law%2Ftop-texas-judge-shocked-by-resignation-of-bankruptcy-colleague%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20influential%20bankruptcy%20courts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20resignation%20led%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Fgovernment%2Fbankruptcy-judges-sudden-resignation-causes-3500-cases-be-reassigned-2023-10-19%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%2C500%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20reassigned%20and%20sparked%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20to%20demand%20Jackson%20Walker%20give%20back%20nearly%20%2423%20million%20in%20fees%20it%20had%20earned%20in%20cases%20that%20Jones%20had%20overseen.%20The%20Southern%20District%20juggernaut%2C%20which%20had%20pulled%20in%20scores%20of%20massive%20cases%20and%20enriched%20the%20Houston%20bankruptcy%20bar%2C%20was%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Isgur%20remained%20unscathed.%20In%20her%20written%20rebuke%20of%20Jones%2C%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20chief%20judge%20took%20care%20to%20note%20that%20%26quot%3Bon%20information%20and%20belief%2C%20the%20judge%20who%20ruled%20on%20the%20motion%20to%20recuse%20was%20unaware%26quot%3B%20that%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20were%20romantic%20partners.%20But%20an%20extensive%20document%20trail%2C%20social%20media%20posts%2C%20and%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20sources%20inside%20Houston's%20legal%20community%20suggest%20that%20narrative%20is%20implausible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman's%20attorney%2C%20Tom%20Kirkendall%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20her%20behalf.%20Isgur%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20sent%20through%20his%20staff.%20Jones'%20attorney%2C%20Gary%20Cruciani%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22946%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20order%20from%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20regarding%20Judge%20David%20Jones%20romantic%20involvement%20with%20an%20attorney%2C%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20who%20appeared%20before%20him%20reads%20in%20part%20%26quot%3BOn%20information%20and%20belief%2C%20the%20judge%20who%20rules%20on%20the%20motion%20to%20recuse%20was%20unaware.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665d1b22cc442a2f676d0a5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20Court%20rebuked%20Judge%20David%20Jones%20but%20said%20that%20his%20longtime%20colleague%2C%20Judge%20Marvin%20Isgur%2C%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bunaware%26quot%3B%20of%20Jones'%20inappropriate%20relationship.%3Cp%3EFifth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%2C%20best%20friends%20know%20the%20identities%20of%20their%20friends'%20long-term%20romantic%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20Nancy%20Rapoport%2C%20an%20influential%20legal%20ethicist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nevada%20Las%20Vegas%20William%20S.%20Boyd%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20paper%20about%20the%20ethical%20questions%20surrounding%20Jones'%20relationship.%20%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BBut%20only%20Judge%20Isgur%20knows%20what%20he%20knew%20or%20didn't%20know%20about%20the%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Southern%20District%20was%20inseparable%20from%20the%20close%20relationships%20between%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%2C%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%2C%20and%20the%20firm%20where%20Freeman%20was%20a%20partner%2C%20Jackson%20Walker.%20The%20Fifth%20Circuit%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%26quot%3B%20money%20was%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I%20love%20him%20like%20a%20father'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur%20and%20Jones%20first%20began%20working%20together%20in%201993%2C%20when%20Isgur%20and%20Kirkendall%2C%20then%20his%20law%20partner%2C%20hired%20Jones%20out%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Houston%20law%20school%20as%20an%20associate%2C%20Jones%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fpodcast-featuring-judges-marvin-isgur-and-david-r%2Fid1196336749%3Fi%3D1000551200858%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFebruary%202022%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20an%20American%20Bankruptcy%20Institute%20podcast.%20Jones%20was%20being%20pursued%20by%20a%20much%20larger%20firm%2C%20he%20told%20someone%20at%20the%20time%2C%20when%20Isgur%20and%20Kirkendall%20persuaded%20him%20to%20join%20their%20small%20litigation%20boutique.%20Both%20men%20spoke%20at%20Jones'%20wedding%20reception%20at%20Brennan's%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brennanshouston.com%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evenerable%20Houston%20restaurant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20who%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20prove%20to%20be%20his%20most%20influential%20professional%20relationship.%20%26quot%3BThey%20took%20me%20in%2C%20taught%20me%20how%20to%20think%2C%20how%20to%20write%2C%20and%20how%20to%20be%20a%20lawyer%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said%20of%20Isgur%20and%20Kirkendall%20in%20March%202023%20when%20he%20accepted%20a%20lifetime%20achievement%20award%20from%20Emory%20Law%20School.%20Isgur%20was%20chosen%20to%20introduce%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Isgur%20and%20Jones%20lived%20a%20short%20distance%20away%20from%20each%20other%20in%20a%20wealthy%20enclave%20on%20Houston's%20west%20side.%20Jones%20would%20go%20sailing%20on%20Galveston%20Bay%20with%20Isgur%20on%20his%20boat.%20The%20two%20men%20often%20ate%20together%20at%20hole-in-the-wall%20restaurants%2C%20according%20to%20two%20people%20familiar%20with%20their%20habits.%20One%20of%20the%20sources%20said%20they%20were%20frequently%20joined%20at%20these%20dinners%20by%20their%20wives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20some%20measures%2C%20the%20two%20men%20made%20an%20odd%20pair.%20The%20elder%20judge%20was%20a%20Houston%20native%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20influential%20Winograd%20real%20estate%20family%2C%20and%20a%20nondrinker.%20He%20wore%20his%20receding%20hair%20cropped%20close%20and%20wire-rimmed%20glasses%20that%20gave%20him%20the%20authority%20of%20a%20man%20steeped%20in%20the%20law.%20Behind%20the%20bench%2C%20he%20was%20always%20in%20control.%20Jones%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20voluble%20and%20audacious.%20A%20North%20Carolina%20native%20estranged%20from%20his%20father%2C%20Jones%20liked%20sharing%20a%20drink%20with%20members%20of%20the%20Houston%20bar.%20As%20a%20judge%2C%20he%20would%20sometimes%20berate%20litigants%20and%20attorneys%20in%20his%20court%2C%20and%20he%20liked%20to%20boast%20about%20how%2C%20as%20an%20attorney%2C%20he%20had%20pushed%20the%20boundaries%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20over%20the%20years%2C%20their%20relationship%20blossomed%20into%20something%20almost%20familial.%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20him%20like%20a%20father%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20once%20said%20of%20Isgur.%20In%20introducing%20Jones%20at%20the%20Emory%20event%2C%20Isgur%20called%20him%20his%20%26quot%3Bstubborn%20adopted%20son.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20better%20feeling%20than%20when%20a%20parent%20watches%20his%20child%20surpass%20him%20in%20capability%20and%20achievement%2C%26quot%3B%20Isgur%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20so%20proud.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur's%20only%20actual%20child%2C%20Sarah%2C%20is%20a%20conservative%20lawyer%20known%20for%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fnews%2Fpersons-of-interest%2Fsarah-isgurs-majority-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20and%20her%20three%20years%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20Most%20recently%2C%20she's%20made%20a%20name%20hosting%20a%20must-listen%20legal%20podcast%2C%20Advisory%20Opinions%2C%20in%20which%20she%20has%20repeatedly%20explored%20questions%20of%20judicial%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jones%20appeared%20on%20the%20podcast%20in%202020%2C%20their%20dynamic%20was%20warm.%20Sarah%20called%20him%20a%20%26quot%3Bfamily%20friend%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Jones%20congratulated%20Isgur%20on%20her%20pregnancy.%20Several%20years%20earlier%2C%20when%20Sarah%20got%20married%20in%20the%20federal%20courthouse%2C%20her%20father%20officiated%20and%20Jones%20and%20his%20then%20wife%20were%20in%20attendance%2C%20according%20to%20one%20wedding%20guest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Isgur%20became%20a%20bankruptcy%20judge%2C%20appointed%20by%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20in%202004%2C%20Jones%20joined%20Porter%20Hedges%2C%20a%20Houston%20law%20firm%20whose%201981%20founding%20made%20it%20a%20relative%20newcomer%20to%20the%20city's%20legal%20scene.%20Porter%20Hedges'%20scrappy%20status%20gave%20Jones%20the%20freedom%20to%20further%20develop%20into%20an%20aggressive%20litigator%2C%20making%20his%20name%20representing%20trustees%20charged%20with%20selling%20off%20assets%20in%20Chapter%207%20bankruptcies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20records%20suggest%20that%20Jones%20may%20have%20first%20crossed%20paths%20with%20Freeman%20in%202002%2C%20when%20he%20was%20still%20in%20private%20practice%20with%20Isgur%3B%20that%20year%2C%20she%20represented%20a%20creditor%20and%20Jones%20a%20trustee%20in%20the%20same%20bankruptcy%20case.%20Over%20four%20days%20in%20March%202008%2C%20each%20attorney%20was%20assigned%20to%20a%20case%20the%20other%20had%20already%20been%20working%20on%20for%20months.%20By%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Freeman%20had%20joined%20Porter%20Hedges%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20work%20with%20Jones%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20practice%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20who%20knew%20them%20at%20the%20time.%20Her%20husband%20had%20recently%20joined%20Porter%20Hedges%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Porter%20Hedges%2C%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20worked%20closely%20together.%20In%20several%20pleadings%20from%20that%20time%2C%20they%20appear%20on%20the%20same%20signature%20block%2C%20indicating%20that%20they%20were%20jointly%20handling%20a%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dozen%20people%20gather%20around%20a%20kitchen%20table%20making%20tamales%20including%20Albert%20Alonzo%2C%20then%20a%20case%20manager%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court%2C%20Judge%20David%20Jones%20in%20the%20gray%20cap%20and%20his%20former%20clerk%20%E2%80%94%20and%20secret%20romantic%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%20in%20a%20green%20T-shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665d2006d0b8e1c832cb1582%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%202022%20tamale%20party%20was%20attended%20by%20Jones%20(in%20the%20gray%20cap)%20and%20his%20former%20clerk%20%E2%80%94%20and%20secret%20romantic%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%20(in%20the%20Keystone%20T-shirt%20at%20left).%3Cp%3EFacebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20when%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20first%20became%20romantically%20involved%2C%20but%20Porter%20Hedges%20appeared%20to%20take%20a%20more%20liberal%20stance%20on%20interoffice%20romance%20than%20many%20Big%20Law%20firms%20did%20at%20the%20time.%20John%20Higgins%2C%20a%20senior%20partner%2C%20started%20dating%20Whitney%20Ables%20when%20they%20worked%20together%20at%20Porter%3B%20they%20were%20later%20married%20in%20a%20ceremony%20Jones%20officiated.%20Josh%20Wolfshohl%20also%20met%20his%20wife%20Amy%20Lucas%20while%20they%20were%20working%20together%20there%3B%20both%20remain%20at%20the%20firm.%20And%20Porter%20hired%20Freeman%20even%20though%20her%20husband%20was%20already%20a%20partner%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur%2C%20during%20his%20time%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20had%20encouraged%20Jones%20to%20consider%20becoming%20a%20bankruptcy%20judge.%20When%20Judge%20Wesley%20Steen%20retired%20from%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court%20in%202011%2C%20Jones%20got%20his%20chance%2C%20and%20applied%20to%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fedbar.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2FBankruptcy-Brief-pdf-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejudges%20appoint%3C%2Fa%3E%20bankruptcy%20judges%20in%20the%20circuit%20%E2%80%94%20to%20fill%20Steen's%20seat.%20Jones%20would%20again%20become%20a%20close%20colleague%20of%20his%20mentor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur%20moved%20quickly%20to%20get%20Jones%20hearing%20cases%2C%20swearing%20him%20in%20at%20a%20private%20ceremony%20in%20advance%20of%20the%20official%20investiture%2C%20a%20small%20gathering%20he%20hosted%20in%20his%20courtroom%20on%20the%20fourth%20floor%20of%20Houston's%20federal%20courthouse.%20About%20two%20dozen%20people%20were%20there%2C%20according%20to%20two%20people%20who%20attended%2C%20including%20Freeman.%20She%20was%20tasked%20with%20taking%20pictures%2C%20and%20at%20one%20point%2C%20her%20emotions%20overcame%20her%20and%20she%20teared%20up%2C%20according%20to%20one%20of%20the%20attendees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20Freeman%20had%20already%20decided%20to%20leave%20her%20job%20at%20Porter%20Hedges%2C%20where%20she%20was%20poised%20to%20earn%20handsomely%20by%20taking%20over%20casework%20from%20Jones.%20That%20year%2C%20partners%20at%20Houston's%20law%20firms%20earned%20on%20average%20nearly%20%24800%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20one%20compensation%20survey.%20Instead%2C%20she%20took%20up%20a%20position%20as%20Jones'%20permanent%20clerk%2C%20likely%20making%20closer%20to%20%24100%2C000%20in%20a%20role%20she%20would%20hold%20for%20the%20next%20six%20years.%20The%20following%20year%2C%20her%20husband%20moved%20to%20dissolve%20their%20marriage%2C%20according%20to%20Harris%20County%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20heard%20she%20went%20and%20became%20his%20law%20clerk%2C%20I%20thought%20that's%20a%20surprise.%20I%20would%20not%20have%20expected%20that%20to%20be%20a%20typical%20career%20path%20for%20Liz%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20former%20colleague%20of%20theirs%20at%20Porter%20Hedges.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20heard%20that%20they%20were%20eventually%20found%20to%20be%20cohabitating%2C%20it%20didn't%20surprise%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20months%20after%20Freeman%20began%20her%20clerkship%2C%20Jones%20too%20got%20divorced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20probably%20should%20have%20talked%20with%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20my%20wife%20%E2%80%94%20now%20my%20ex-wife%20%E2%80%94%20about%20that%20decision%2C%20because%20that's%20obviously%20a%20huge%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20told%20Reuters%20in%202020.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20something%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20do%20and%20if%20I%20was%20going%20to%20do%20it%2C%20I%20was%20going%20to%20devote%20the%20same%20energy%20into%20being%20a%20judge%20that%20I%20did%20into%20being%20a%20lawyer.%26quot%3B%20He%20suggested%20in%20another%20interview%20that%20the%20couple%20experienced%20tension%20over%20the%20decrease%20in%20his%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20kept%20the%20house%20he%20had%20shared%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20and%20sometime%20later%2C%20Freeman%20moved%20in%20with%20him%2C%20according%20to%20one%20person%20aware%20of%20the%20arrangement.%20The%20real%20estate%20photos%20Jones%20used%20later%20to%20sell%20the%20home%20showed%20what%20looked%20like%20a%20boy's%20bedroom%2C%20even%20though%20Freeman%20was%20the%20only%20one%20in%20the%20couple%20with%20kids%2C%20and%20a%20closet%20that%20held%20women's%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Jones%20purchased%20a%20house%20in%20a%20gentrifying%20neighborhood%20in%20northwest%20Houston%2C%20not%20far%20from%20his%20previous%20home.%20He%20and%20Freeman%20toured%20the%20home%20together%2C%20and%20Jones%20ultimately%20paid%20%24985%2C000%20in%20cash%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fbankruptcy-law%2Fsex-and-secrets-trigger-downfall-of-star-texas-bankruptcy-judge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20reported%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Real%20estate%20records%20show%20that%20they%20came%20to%20jointly%20own%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20Isgur%20visited%20Jones%20at%20the%20homes%20he%20shared%20with%20Freeman%20is%20unclear%2C%20but%20the%20elder%20judge%20would%20have%20witnessed%20the%20dynamic%20between%20the%20pair%20over%20the%20six%20years%20they%20all%20worked%20closely%20together%20at%20the%20Houston%20courthouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20set%20up%20the%20special%20panel%20because%20they%20are%20great%20judges%2C%20and%20they%20are%20great%20arbiters%20of%20the%20law%2C%20and%20then%20to%20say%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20sensibility%20with%20the%20people%20they%20have%20lunch%20with%20beggars%20disbelief%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bruce%20Markell%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20bankruptcy%20judge%20in%20Nevada%20who%20now%20teaches%20law%20at%20Northwestern's%20Pritzker%20School%20of%20Law.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20Isgur%20didn't%20know%20her.%20Whether%20he%20knew%20about%20the%20relationship%20or%20not%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20think%20that%20Isgur%20was%20taken%20completely%20by%20surprise%20by%20the%20allegations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20plan%20to%20grow%20the%20Houston%20court%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jones%20joined%20the%20bankruptcy%20court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20Delaware%20and%20New%20York%20dominated%20as%20the%20venue%20of%20choice%20for%20major%20corporate%20bankruptcies.%20But%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%20came%20up%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20make%20Houston%20a%20magnet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20bankruptcies%20are%20big%20business.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20process%20has%20been%20used%20by%20companies%20with%20too%20much%20debt%20and%20not%20enough%20cash%20to%20find%20fresh%20footing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20over%20time%2C%20it's%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20lucrative%20areas%20of%20law.%20%3Cspan%3ETop%20attorneys%20can%20make%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fbankruptcy-law%2Fbig-law-bankruptcy-fees-reach-2-500-an-hour-for-top-lawyers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eup%20to%20%242%2C500%20an%20hour%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20bankruptcy%20cases%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20money%20that%20can%20warp%20a%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20In%20recent%20decades%2C%20bankruptcy%20forum%20shopping%20has%20become%20rampant%2C%20with%20firms%20filing%20in%20whatever%20federal%20district%20they%20like%2C%20just%20by%20showing%20a%20local%20address%20there.%20Sometimes%20a%20PO%20Box%20is%20enough.%20So%20lawyers%20tend%20to%20congregate%20where%20they%20find%20corporate-friendly%20judges%20who%20have%20a%20reputation%20for%20quickly%20moving%20companies%20through%20the%20process%20and%20signing%20off%20on%20lawyers'%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Delaware%20and%20New%20York%20dominated%20as%20the%20venues%20of%20choice%20for%20major%20bankruptcies%2C%20millions%20of%20dollars%20flowed%20into%20the%20coffers%20of%20local%20law%20firms%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20judges%20became%20their%20own%20power%20centers%2C%20with%20every%20decision%20affecting%20the%20paychecks%20of%20local%20lawyers%20and%20the%20fortunes%20of%20their%20firms%3A%20%3Cspan%3EDecide%20against%20the%20debtor%20and%20their%20law%20firm%20might%20seek%20a%20different%20venue%20for%20their%20next%20client.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%20judges%20had%20tried%20to%20break%20into%20the%20upper%20ranks%20before%2C%20without%20success.%20Judge%20William%20Greendyke%20promised%20attorneys%20in%202000%20that%20the%20judges'%20%26quot%3Bwar%20on%20fees%20is%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Lynn%20LoPucki's%20book%20%3Cem%3ECourting%20Failure%3C%2Fem%3E.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Houston-based%20Enron%20still%20chose%20New%20York%20for%20its%20spectacular%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20diagram%20of%20the%20social%20and%20professional%20worlds%20of%20Houston%20bankruptcy%20judges%20David%20Jones%20and%20Marvin%20Isgur%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665d1ec2d0b8e1c832cb1578%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22627%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDiagram%3A%20Business%20Insider%3B%20photos%3A%20Reuters%3B%20LinkedIn%3B%20Facebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%20began%20to%20hatch%20a%20more%20ambitious%20plan%20to%20make%20Houston%20welcoming.%20Success%20would%20mean%20more%20money%20for%20the%20men%20and%20women%20of%20the%20local%20bankruptcy%20bar%2C%20and%20more%20power%20and%20prestige%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%20They%20created%20a%20special%20panel%20for%20complex%20cases%2C%20changing%20Southern%20District%20rules%20so%20extremely%20large%20or%20complex%20Chapter%2011%20bankruptcies%20%E2%80%94%20including%2C%20now%2C%20those%20involving%20at%20least%20%24200%20million%20in%20debt%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0would%20get%20an%20unusual%20degree%20of%20predictability.%20Even%20though%20the%20Judicial%20Conference%2C%20which%20sets%20policy%20for%20the%20federal%20courts%2C%20had%20long%20supported%20the%20random%20assignment%20of%20federal%20judges%20in%20order%20to%20deter%20judge-shopping%2C%20the%20new%20Southern%20District%20scheme%20would%20assign%20every%20complex%20case%20to%20just%20one%20of%20two%20judges%3A%20Jones%20or%20Isgur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOvernight%2C%20bankruptcy%20lawyers%20that%20typically%20worked%20on%20large%2C%20complex%20cases%20before%20any%20one%20of%203%20or%204%20sitting%20bankruptcy%20judges%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20Walker%20wrote%20in%20a%20court%20filing%20last%20month%2C%20%26quot%3Bnow%20would%20be%20practicing%20almost%20exclusively%20(and%20routinely)%20before%201%20of%202%20bankruptcy%20judges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20effort%2C%20the%20firm%20said%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20procedures%20more%20transparent%20and%20predictable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20two%20men%20sought%20to%20achieve%20an%20extraordinary%20degree%20of%20consistency%20across%20their%20two%20dockets%20and%20would%20often%20discuss%20each%20other's%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20who%20heard%20it%20directly%20from%20Jones.%20The%20two%20men%20would%20walk%20back%20and%20forth%20to%20each%20other's%20chambers%20on%20the%20courthouse's%20fourth%20floor.%20%26quot%3BWe%20talk%20every%20day%2C%20multiple%20times%2C%20whether%20he%20wants%20to%20or%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said%20in%20his%20remarks%20last%20year%20at%20Emory.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20imagine%20him%20not%20being%20right%20down%20the%20hall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20threw%20open%20the%20doors%20to%20the%20bankruptcy%20bar%2C%20creating%20a%20committee%20of%20bankruptcy%20attorneys%20to%20advise%20the%20judges%20on%20industry%20best%20practices.%20Among%20the%20founding%20members%20were%20Patricia%20Tomasco%2C%20then%20a%20partner%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%3B%20Christopher%20Lopez%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20Weil%2C%20Gotshal%20%26amp%3B%20Manges%20who%20would%20go%20on%20to%20become%20a%20Southern%20District%20judge%3B%20and%20Greendyke%2C%20who%20had%20by%20then%20retired%20as%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reform%20was%20to%20promise%20attorneys%20for%20major%20corporations%20concierge%20access%20to%20court%20officials%20to%20expedite%20scheduling%20and%20process%20matters.%20Jones%20assigned%20his%20case%20manager%2C%20Albert%20Alonzo%2C%20a%20government-issued%20cell%20phone%20and%20told%20him%20to%20answer%20it%20whenever%20it%20rang.%20Jones%20would%20call%20him%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20to%20test%20his%20resolve%20and%20Alonzo%20always%20answered%2C%20the%20judge%20told%20Reuters%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20is%20the%20public's%20way%20to%20talk%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20told%20the%20Texas%20Lawbook%20in%202020.%20%26quot%3BHe%20has%20tremendous%20scheduling%20authority.%20He's%20great%20at%20customer%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20worked%20together%2C%20the%20two%20men%20grew%20close.%20Jones%20said%20he%20spent%20time%20with%20Alonzo's%20family%20during%20the%20holidays%20and%20at%20least%20once%20he%20and%20Freeman%20attended%20Alonzo's%20annual%20tamale-making%20party%20together%2C%20according%20to%20a%20social%20media%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20close%20circle%20of%20lawyers%20around%20Jones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur%20was%20known%20to%20avoid%20spending%20time%20with%20Houston's%20bankruptcy%20bar%20outside%20of%20the%20courthouse%20or%20official%20conferences.%20But%20just%20down%20the%20hall%2C%20Jones%20routinely%20blurred%20the%20boundaries%20between%20his%20professional%20and%20personal%20lives%2C%20becoming%20friends%20with%20a%20group%20of%20attorneys%20who%20often%20appeared%20before%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJones%20had%20issued%20an%20order%20in%202016%20arguing%20against%20%26quot%3Bunspoken%20practices%2C%20or%20disparate%20treatment%26quot%3B%20even%20as%20he%20was%20offering%20special%20access%2C%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20ways%2C%20for%20this%20small%20network%20of%20lawyers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20two%20attorneys%20close%20to%20Jones'%20circle%2C%20a%20small%20group%20of%20lawyers%20would%20often%20hang%20around%20Jones'%20chambers%2C%20which%20he%20decorated%20with%20framed%20news%20articles%20about%20him.%20One%2C%20a%202020%20Houston%20Chronicle%20profile%2C%20was%20headlined%3A%20%26quot%3BMeet%20the%20judge%20who%20saved%20the%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20practice.%26quot%3B%20(After%20that%20article%20came%20out%2C%20someone%20taped%20up%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20outside%20the%20fourth%20floor%20elevators%20with%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bsavior%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20arrow%20pointing%20to%20Jones'%20courtroom%2C%20a%20third%20attorney%20recalls.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20locked%20entrance%20to%20his%20chambers%20became%20such%20a%20revolving%20door%20that%20when%20Van%20Deelen%20pressed%20the%20buzzer%20in%20October%202023%2C%20intending%20to%20hand%20his%20retaliation%20lawsuit%20to%20Jones%2C%20he%20was%20let%20in%20with%20no%20questions%20asked%2C%20he%20said.%20Alonzo%20once%20posted%20that%20a%20lawyer%20close%20to%20Jones%2C%20Susan%20Tran%20Adams%2C%20stopped%20by%20with%20coffee%20and%20empanadas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20his%20frequent%20visits%20to%20Jones'%20chambers%2C%20Isgur%20likely%20saw%20the%20crowd%2C%20which%20often%20included%20Freeman.%20Two%20attorneys%20specifically%20recall%20Isgur%20entering%20Jones'%20chambers%20while%20other%20lawyers%20were%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20said%20he%20and%20some%20of%20the%20lawyers%20formed%20a%20cooking%20team%20that%20would%20enter%20local%20barbecue%20and%20chili%20competitions%2C%20and%20several%20in%20the%20group%20recently%20started%20a%20nonprofit%20together.%20Social%20media%20posts%20over%20the%20years%20of%20informal%20gatherings%20show%20Jones%2C%20Freeman%2C%20and%20Alonzo%20hamming%20it%20up%20with%20other%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20year%2C%20a%20Houston%20bankruptcy%20attorney%20invited%20a%20group%20of%20lawyers%2C%20including%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorneys%20Matt%20Cavenaugh%2C%20Veronica%20Polnick%2C%20and%20Genevieve%20Graham%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Freeman%2C%20then%20running%20her%20own%20practice%2C%20to%20a%20party%20for%20Jones%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20who%20was%20told%20about%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22589%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20October%202022%20cookout%20featuring%20multiple%20members%20of%20the%20Houston%20bar%2C%20including%20Judge%20David%20Jones%2C%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20back%20row%3B%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%20Veronica%20Polnick%2C%20in%20the%20back%20row%20with%20sunglasses%20on%20her%20forehead%3B%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%20Genevieve%20Graham%2C%20squatting%20center%20with%20a%20red%20cup%3B%20then%20case%20manager%20Albert%20Alonzo%2C%20front%20row%20in%20the%20white%20cap%3B%20and%20then%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20sitting%20center%20with%20red%20sneakers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665d1f29d0b8e1c832cb157c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22743%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20October%202022%20cookout%20featured%20multiple%20members%20of%20the%20Houston%20bar%2C%20including%20Jones%20(back%20row%2C%20gray%20hair)%20and%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorneys%20Veronica%20Polnick%20(back%20row%2C%20sunglasses%20on%20forehead)%2C%20Genevieve%20Graham%20(squatting%20center%20with%20red%20cup)%2C%20and%20Freeman%20(sitting%20center%20with%20red%20sneakers).%3Cp%3EFacebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20root%20of%20many%20of%20these%20friendships%20was%20a%20drop-in%20evidence%20class%20Jones%20began%20to%20lead%20for%20Houston%20lawyers%20soon%20after%20he%20joined%20the%20bench.%20The%20free%20class%20started%20small%20and%20invite-only%2C%20but%20after%20several%20years%20grew%20to%20number%2040%20or%2050%20students%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20who%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulars%20included%20attorneys%20who%20worked%20at%2C%20or%20would%20later%20join%2C%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20according%20to%20emails%2C%20such%20as%20Polnick%2C%20Graham%2C%20and%20Cavenaugh.%20According%20to%20a%20recent%20Jackson%20Walker%20legal%20filing%2C%20%26quot%3Bother%20bankruptcy%20judges%20and%20prominent%20local%20practitioners%20attended%20the%20classes%26quot%3B%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20well%20attended%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another%20Houston%20bankruptcy%20attorney.%20%26quot%3BI%20attended%20a%20couple%2C%20and%20you%20could%20really%20see%20the%20young%20attorneys%20clicking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20clicked%20with%20them%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20several%20young%20lawyers%20that%20are%20present%20tonight%20that%20I%20first%20met%20in%20a%20weekly%20class%20that%20I%20teach%20in%20my%20courtroom%20on%20most%20Wednesdays%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said%20in%20his%20prepared%20remarks%20for%20the%20Emory%20event%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20class%20was%20as%20much%20of%20a%20learning%20session%20for%20me%20as%20it%20was%20a%20teaching%20session.%20Not%20only%20did%20we%20become%20better%20professionals%20together%2C%20we%20became%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20officiated%20the%20marriages%20of%20at%20least%20two%20lawyers%20who%20attended%20those%20classes%3A%20Tran%20and%20Graham.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20class%20was%20effectively%20yet%20another%20Jones%20strategy%20for%20attracting%20bankruptcy%20filings%20to%20the%20Southern%20District%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20way%20for%20members%20of%20the%20Houston%20bar%20to%20explore%20tactics%20they%20might%20later%20deploy%20in%20Jones'%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20classes%20were%20sometimes%20also%20a%20ticket%20to%20career%20advancement.%20At%20least%20one%20young%20law%20graduate%2C%20Christina%20Morrison%2C%20used%20the%20classes%20to%20successfully%20audition%20for%20a%20clerkship%20with%20Jones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsgur%20was%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20tight%20legal%20community%20around%20Jones'%20evidence%20class.%20He%20told%20the%20assembled%20crowd%20at%20Emory%20how%20%26quot%3Byoung%20lawyers%20show%20up%20weekly%20%E2%80%94%20dozens%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20to%20learn%20trial%20tactics%20and%20bankruptcy%20from%20David.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20tried%20and%20failed%20to%20find%20an%20opportunity%20to%20introduce%20myself%20to%20Isgur%20at%20the%20courthouse%2C%20I%20visited%20Isgur's%20home%20in%20April%2C%20hoping%20to%20find%20out%20how%20the%20judge%20was%20currently%20feeling%20about%20his%20adopted%20son%20and%20to%20ask%20when%20he%20first%20became%20aware%20of%20Jones'%20relationship%20with%20Freeman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20who%20appeared%20to%20be%20his%20wife%20answered%2C%20keeping%20the%20door%20closed%20and%20speaking%20through%20a%20side%20window%20of%20the%20stately%20brick%20home.%20%26quot%3BGet%20the%20hell%20away%20from%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20after%20I%20identified%20myself%20as%20a%20journalist.%20When%20I%20turned%20to%20leave%2C%20the%20woman%20noticed%20that%20my%20hair%20was%20pulled%20back%20in%20a%20ponytail.%20She%20commented%20on%20the%20style%2C%20and%20when%20I%20turned%20back%20to%20face%20her%2C%20she%20began%20to%20mock%20me%2C%20moving%20her%20hips%20in%20a%20side-to-side%20dance.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20want%20to%20wear%20a%20skirt%20or%20earrings%3F%20Are%20you%20trans%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20her%20voice%20rose%2C%20she%20hurled%20an%20expletive%20and%20screamed%2C%20%26quot%3BGet%20off%20the%20property!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERumors%20of%20a%20romantic%20relationship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20and%20Isgur's%20efforts%20soon%20began%20to%20attract%20hundreds%20of%20filings%20to%20the%20district.%20Big%20names%20showed%20up%3A%20Neiman%20Marcus%20and%20J.C.%20Penney%2C%20then%20Chesapeake%20Energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETomasco%2C%20the%20Jackson%20Walker%20partner%20who%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20complex%20cases%20committee%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20already%20been%20doing%20her%20part%20to%20build%20up%20the%20court%20and%20drum%20up%20business%20for%20her%20firm%20by%20flying%20to%20New%20York%20in%20a%20campaign%20to%20convince%20the%20Big%20Law%20bankruptcy%20attorneys%20to%20bring%20their%20cases%20south.%20But%20the%20flow%20of%20cases%20only%20escalated%20after%20Freeman%20left%20her%20clerkship%2C%20in%20May%202018%2C%20and%20joined%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20quickly%20became%20known%20as%20someone%20who%20bristled%20over%20complying%20with%20protocols%20and%20failed%20to%20loop%20her%20colleagues%20in%20on%20critical%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20Cavenaugh%20set%20up%20a%20business%20agreement%20that%2C%20according%20to%20two%20of%20their%20professional%20contacts%2C%20appeared%20to%20be%20premised%20on%20Freeman's%20tight%20relationship%20with%20Jones%20paying%20off.%20Though%20Freeman%20hadn't%20worked%20at%20a%20law%20firm%20in%20six%20years%2C%20Cavenaugh%20and%20Freeman%20agreed%20to%20split%20the%20origination%20income%20they%20got%20for%20bringing%20in%20new%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20the%20two%20sources%2C%20who%20were%20told%20about%20the%20arrangement.%20Like%20anyone%20exiting%20public%20service%2C%20Freeman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lw.com%2Fadmin%2Fupload%2FSiteAttachments%2FJudges-Start-at-the-Beginning-After-Leaving-Bench-for-Big-Law.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehadn't%20done%20marketing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20years.%20If%20she%20hadn't%20delivered%2C%20it%20could%20have%20meant%20a%20substantial%20compensation%20loss%20for%20Cavenaugh.%20Instead%2C%20according%20to%20a%20November%20Jackson%20Walker%20filing%2C%20Freeman%20enjoyed%20%26quot%3Bquick%20and%20substantial%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSharing%20origination%20fees%20is%20common%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20and%20it%20is%20well%20known%20that%20sharing%20is%20part%20of%20our%20culture%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%26quot%3B%20firm%20spokesperson%20Jim%20Wilkinson%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BWe%20quite%20often%20share%20origination%20fees%20among%20attorneys%20irrespective%20of%20location%20and%20there%20is%20nothing%20out%20of%20the%20ordinary%20with%20our%20compensation%20practices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20the%20rumors%20about%20Jones%20and%20Freeman's%20romantic%20relationship%20were%20frequent%20enough%20that%20at%20least%20one%20attorney%20confronted%20Jones%20about%20it%3B%20Jones%20responded%20by%20denying%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20see%20them%20going%20to%20lunch%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20colleague%20from%20Porter%20Hedges.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20unusual%20for%20judges%20and%20their%20clerks%20to%20go%20to%20lunch%20together%20but%20we%20typically%20think%20of%20a%20federal%20judge's%20law%20clerk%20in%20bankruptcy%20or%20district%20court%20as%20a%20substantially%20younger%20person%20relatively%20recently%20out%20of%20school.%20The%20optics%20were%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Jackson%20Walker%20had%20a%20partner%20with%20a%20direct%20line%20to%20the%20leading%20judge%20of%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20court.%20Business%20boomed.%20During%20Jones'%20career%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20two%20firms%2C%20Kirkland%20%26amp%3B%20Ellis%20and%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20represented%20the%20most%20debtors%20with%20confirmed%20Chapter%2011%20plans%2C%20according%20to%20data%20provider%20Lex%20Machina.%20And%20Kirkland%20%26amp%3B%20Ellis%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0whose%20attorneys%20were%20invited%20to%20Jones'%20evidence%20class%20as%20special%20guests%20at%20least%20twice%2C%20according%20to%20emails%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0often%20relied%20on%20Jackson%20Walker%20as%20its%20local%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202012%20and%202017%2C%20before%20Freeman%20left%20for%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20just%2027%20companies%20with%20liabilities%20of%20%24100%20million%20or%20more%20filed%20their%20bankruptcy%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20according%20to%20BankruptcyData.%20From%202018%20through%202023%20that%20number%20more%20than%20quadrupled%20to%20148.%20During%20the%20three%20years%20ending%20in%202023%2C%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%20together%20handled%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20all%20bankruptcy%20cases%20with%20liabilities%20over%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJackson%20Walker%20was%20involved%20in%20a%20large%20number%20of%20them%2C%20with%20Freeman%2C%20as%20the%20US%20Trustee%20said%2C%20creating%20an%20%26quot%3Bunlevel%20'playing%20field.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Trustee%20Program%20has%20filed%20several%20motions%20to%20force%20the%20law%20firm%20to%20disgorge%20a%20total%20of%20nearly%20%2423%20million%20in%20what%20it%20called%20%26quot%3Btainted%26quot%3B%20fees%20collected%20in%20cases%20involving%20Jackson%20Walker%20that%20were%20heard%20by%20Jones%20as%20far%20back%20as%202018.%20More%20than%20%242%20million%20of%20those%20fees%20were%20personally%20collected%20by%20Freeman.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20clerk%2C%20Freeman%20was%20present%20while%20Jones%20and%20Isgur%20were%20concocting%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20complex%20cases%20committee.%20As%20a%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%2C%20she%20became%20a%20formal%20member.%20But%20Freeman%20continued%20to%20act%20as%20if%20she%20were%20an%20insider.%20When%20Tomasco%2C%20for%20example%2C%20asked%20the%20committee%20members%20in%20a%20December%2027%2C%202021%2C%20email%20if%20the%20court's%20hybrid%20hearing%20schedule%20would%20change%2C%20Freeman%20responded%2C%20according%20to%20correspondence%20BI%20obtained%20through%20a%20public%20records%20request.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20continue%20until%20further%20notice%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20from%20her%20Jackson%20Walker%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20this%20point%2C%20Isgur%20had%20become%20one%20of%20the%20busiest%20bankruptcy%20judges%20in%20the%20country.%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorneys%20including%20Cavenaugh%20and%20Freeman%20were%20frequently%20appearing%20in%20front%20of%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20companies%20were%20now%20aggressively%20venue%20shopping%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankruptcy%20rules%20require%20a%20company%20to%20be%20based%20in%20the%20district%20for%20180%20days.%20But%20court%20filings%20in%20the%202023%20bankruptcy%20of%20the%20biopharmaceutical%20company%20Sorrento%20show%20that%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%20Veronica%20Polnick%20%E2%80%94%20another%20former%20Jones%20clerk%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0visited%20a%20UPS%20Store%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Houston%20to%20open%20a%20mailbox%20less%20than%2010%20hours%20before%20the%20company%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20UPS%20store%20soon%20became%20the%20principal%20place%20of%20business%20for%20other%20Jackson%20Walker%20clients%2C%20according%20to%20legal%20filings%3A%20medical%20technology%20firm%20Surgalign%20Spine%20Technologies%2C%20sweet%20treat%20subscription%20company%20Candy%20Club%20LLC%2C%20and%20industrial%20food%20startup%20AppHarvest%20Products%2C%20all%20with%20mailboxes%20registered%20by%20Polnick%20%E2%80%94%20in%20one%20instance%20for%20a%20case%20filed%20by%20Cavenaugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20bankruptcy%20business%20was%20coming%20into%20Houston%20that%20attorneys%20there%20were%20getting%20bold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202022%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20bar%20met%20for%20a%20conference%20at%20the%20Omni%20Hotel%20in%20Corpus%20Christi%2C%20a%20chance%20for%20attorneys%20to%20get%20continuing%20education%20credits%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20face%20time%20with%20judges.%20A%20panel%20titled%20%26quot%3BJudges%20Panel%20%E2%80%94%20Ask%20Anything%20You%20Want!%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20three-day%20event%20gave%20attorneys%20an%20open%20forum%20to%20ask%20questions%20of%20Jones%2C%20Isgur%2C%20and%20the%20other%20bankruptcy%20judges%20of%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Cavenaugh%20roamed%20the%20room%20with%20the%20mic%2C%20one%20attorney%20spoke%20up%2C%20saying%20clients%20had%20reported%20that%20other%20attorneys%20were%20suggesting%20they%20had%20a%20special%20connection%20with%20the%20judges%20of%20the%20Southern%20District.%20The%20attorney%20asked%20the%20judges%20how%20lawyers%20should%20respond%20the%20next%20time%20they%20heard%20something%20about%20these%20attorneys'%20special%20status%2C%20according%20to%20someone%20in%20attendance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%2C%20in%20prefacing%20a%20noncommittal%20answer%2C%20suggested%20that%20the%20question%20was%20likely%20directed%20at%20him%2C%20the%20source%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20Cavenaugh%20and%20Jackson%20Walker%20were%20aware%20of%20the%20allegations%20of%20a%20Jones-Freeman%20relationship%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20the%20firm%20later%20filed%20in%20court.%20Van%20Deelen%20had%20received%20the%20explosive%20anonymous%20note%2013%20months%20before%2C%20and%20an%20email%20he%20sent%20to%20Cavenaugh%20right%20after%20receiving%20it%20had%20sparked%20an%20apparently%20cursory%20internal%20Jackson%20Walker%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20admitted%20that%20she%20and%20Jones%20had%20been%20in%20a%20relationship%2C%20but%20said%20it%20had%20ended%2C%20according%20to%20a%20draft%20letter%20the%20firm's%20then-general%20counsel%20wrote%20in%20August%202021%20to%20an%20outside%20ethics%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BElizabeth%20has%20confirmed%20that%20there%20is%20no%20current%20romantic%20relationship%20between%20herself%20and%20Judge%20Jones%20and%20that%20none%20is%20expected%20going%20forward.%20According%20to%20Elizabeth%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20romantic%20relationship%20since%20prior%20to%20the%20time%20in%20March%202020%20when%20COVID%20caused%20so%20many%20of%20us%20to%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20and%20virtual-only%20meetings.%20Judge%20Jones%20and%20Elizabeth%20each%20own%20their%20own%20homes%3B%20they%20do%20not%20and%20have%20not%20lived%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20described%20Freeman's%20critical%20role%20bringing%20in%20new%20business%20to%20the%20firm%20since%20she%20had%20joined%20in%202018.%20%26quot%3BJackson%20Walker's%20debtor%20practice%20grew%20very%20substantially%20during%20this%20time%2C%20including%20cases%20in%20which%20we%20took%20an%20expansive%20local%20counsel%20role%2C%20with%20Kirkland%20Ellis%20acting%20as%20lead%20counsel%2C%20and%20cases%20in%20which%20we%20were%20lead%20debtor's%20counsel.%20Much%20of%20this%20work%20was%20in%20cases%20before%20either%20Judge%20Isgur%20or%20Judge%20Jones.%20This%20success%20was%20a%20team%20effort%2C%20involving%20other%20bankruptcy%20partners%20as%20well%2C%20but%20Elizabeth's%20leadership%20and%20contribution%20were%20recognized%20as%20integral.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20said%20Jackson%20Walker%20had%20requested%20that%20Freeman%20stop%20working%20on%20cases%20once%20they'd%20been%20filed%20with%20Jones%20for%20a%20two-year%20cooling%20off%20period%20from%20the%20date%20Freeman%20claimed%20their%20romance%20had%20ended%3Cspan%3E.%20While%20the%20firm%20understood%20%26quot%3Bthat%20a%20close%20personal%20relationship%20remains%26quot%3B%20between%20Freeman%20and%20Jones%2C%20the%20letter%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%20further%20details%20were%20sought%20at%20that%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20Walker%20later%20learned%20Freeman%20hadn't%20been%20truthful.%20The%20firm's%20counsel%20at%20Norton%20Rose%20Fulbright%20%E2%80%94%20Greendyke%2C%20the%20former%20bankruptcy%20judge%20%E2%80%94%20said%20in%20a%20November%20pleading%20that%20in%202022%20Jackson%20Walker%20had%20%26quot%3Blearned%2C%20quite%20by%20accident%2C%20that%20Ms.%20Freeman's%20denial%20was%20possibly%20false%20or%20at%20least%20no%20longer%20true.%20When%20confronted%20again%20she%20initially%20denied%20the%20relationship%20but%20later%20on%20admitted%20to%20a%20current%20romantic%20relationship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Freeman%20retained%20counsel%2C%20she%20chose%20someone%20with%20close%20ties%20to%20her%20romantic%20partner%3A%20Tom%20Kirkendall%2C%20Jones'%20first%20boss%20in%20the%20legal%20profession%20and%20someone%20who%20described%20Isgur%20to%20Business%20Insider%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20wonderful%20law%20partner%20of%20mine%20for%20over%2010%20years%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20dear%20friend.%26quot%3B%20(Kirkendall%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20other%20aspects%20of%20this%20story.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20year%2C%20Jones%20called%20Cavenaugh%20to%20his%20chambers%20after%20a%20hearing%20and%20%26quot%3Binsinuated%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bunhappy%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20firm's%20push%20to%20disclose%20the%20relationship%2C%20the%20firm%20said%20in%20another%20filing.%20Instead%2C%20Jackson%20Walker%20said%2C%20Jones%20handed%20Cavenaugh%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20with%20a%20proposed%20disclosure%20that%20listed%20a%20%26quot%3Bclose%20personal%20relationship%26quot%3B%20with%20Freeman%20sandwiched%20between%20references%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20friendship%26quot%3B%20with%20Polnick%20and%20with%20Graham.%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20Jones%20insisted%2C%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20make%20this%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20instructing%20the%20firm%20to%20file%20the%20disclosure%20in%20all%20future%20cases%20before%20him%2C%20according%20to%20the%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20the%20language%20%26quot%3Bpotentially%20misleading%20or%20untruthful%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20Walker%20said%20it%20negotiated%20Freeman's%20departure%20instead%3B%20she%20left%20the%20firm%20in%20December%202022%20to%20set%20up%20her%20own%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Jackson%20Walker%20appeared%20to%20keep%20knowledge%20of%20the%20relationship%20to%20itself.%20The%20firm's%20attorneys%20continued%20to%20recommend%20Freeman%20for%20legal%20work%20on%20cases%20before%20the%20Southern%20District.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJackson%20Walker%20has%20a%20strong%20and%20proven%20culture%20of%20ethics%20and%20integrity%2C%20and%20when%20we%20learned%20about%20this%20issue%2C%20we%20acted%20responsibly%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilkinson%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20firm%2C%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BOur%20firm%20has%20been%20transparent%2C%20and%20our%20fulsome%20public%20filings%20speak%20for%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConflicts%20of%20interest%20appeared%20immediately.%20Within%20weeks%2C%20Freeman%2C%20serving%20as%20contract%20attorney%20to%20bond%20issuer%20GWG%20Holdings%20Inc.%2C%20whose%20bankruptcy%20case%20was%20being%20handled%20by%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20told%20Judge%20Isgur%20she%20took%20%26quot%3Bsome%20comfort%26quot%3B%20knowing%20that%20Jones%20was%20serving%20as%20mediator%20in%20the%20case%2C%20according%20to%20a%20December%2016%2C%202022%2C%20transcript.%20During%20the%20mediation%2C%20in%20which%20Freeman%20participated%2C%20Jones%20suggested%20naming%20an%20independent%20trustee%2C%20according%20to%20public%20remarks%20by%20Mike%20Warner%2C%20a%20lawyer%20involved%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20was%20ultimately%20chosen%20by%20the%20creditors%20to%20oversee%20the%20wind-down%20trust%20in%20that%20case%2C%20a%20role%20expected%20to%20earn%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Flaw-firm-tied-bankruptcy-judge-resignation-did-not-make-conflict-disclosures-2023-10-30%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24100%2C000%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Neither%20Jones%2C%20nor%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20nor%20Freeman%20disclosed%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EContaining%20the%20fallout%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20romantic%20relationship%20became%20public%20last%20October%20and%20Jones%20resigned%2C%20Isgur%20found%20himself%20once%20again%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20recusal%20matter.%20The%20estate%20of%20a%20creditor%20in%204E%20Brands%2C%20a%20manufacturer%20of%20hand%20sanitizer%2C%20whose%20bankruptcy%20case%20was%20transferred%20from%20Jones%20to%20Isgur%2C%20argued%20in%20October%20that%20Isgur%20was%20too%20close%20to%20Jones%20to%20rule%20on%20the%20case%20independently.%20The%20US%20Trustee%2C%20which%20oversees%20federal%20bankruptcy%20cases%2C%20supported%20the%20motion%2C%20arguing%20the%20case%20should%20never%20have%20been%20heard%20by%20Jones%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20in%20an%20apparent%20attempt%20to%20contain%20the%20fallout%20from%20Jones'%20ethics%20implosion%2C%20the%20Southern%20District's%20chief%20bankruptcy%20judge%2C%20Eduardo%20Rodriguez%2C%20ruled%20against%20the%20creditor.%20Isgur%20can%20continue%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20he%20ruled%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.txsb.454599%2Fgov.uscourts.txsb.454599.573.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewriting%20in%20the%20December%202023%20opinion%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20lawyers%20for%20the%20creditor%20%26quot%3Bfailed%20to%20demonstrate%20much%20other%20than%20that%20former%20Judge%20Jones%20and%20Judge%20Isgur%20are%20close%20friends.%26quot%3B%20(The%20creditor%20has%20filed%20an%20appeal.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodriguez%20wrote%20that%20the%20estate%20had%20provided%20no%20evidence%20Isgur%20had%20%26quot%3Bextrajudicial%20knowledge%26quot%3B%20of%20Jones'%20relationship%20or%20showed%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20degree%20of%20antagonism%26quot%3B%20in%20denying%20Van%20Deelen's%20March%202021%20recusal%20motion%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0despite%20the%20magnitude%20of%20Isgur's%20missed%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Sorrento%20case%2C%20a%20litigant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fcb3e71a5-ab12-47db-84dd-41b44cd808b6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20remove%20the%20case%20from%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%20Again%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee%20lent%20its%20support%2C%20calling%20Sorrento's%20PO%20Box%20maneuver%20%26quot%3Ba%20case%20of%20forum%20shopping%20and%20venue%20manipulation%20taken%20to%20a%20new%20and%20unprecedented%20extreme.%26quot%3B%20Again%2C%20a%20Southern%20District%20judge%20shut%20it%20down.%20This%20time%2C%20Judge%20Lopez%20%E2%80%94%20a%20member%20of%20the%20complex%20cases%20committee%20turned%20judge%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.txsb.461049%2Fgov.uscourts.txsb.461049.2017.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edenied%20the%20motion.%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Lopez%20had%20replaced%20Isgur%20when%20Isgur%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20complex%20cases%20panel%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%3B%20Isgur%20returned%20to%20the%20panel%20as%20Lopez's%20partner%20after%20Jones%20resigned%20in%20disgrace.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Southern%20District%20has%20stuck%20to%20the%20model%20Jones%20created%2C%20of%20sending%20every%20complex%20case%20to%20a%20panel%20of%20two%20judges%2C%20flouting%20new%20guidance%20issued%20by%20the%20Judicial%20Conference%20of%20the%20US%20in%20March%20that%20further%20promotes%20random%20case%20assignment%20to%20limit%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ability%20of%20litigants%20to%20effectively%20choose%20judges%20in%20certain%20cases%20by%20where%20they%20file%20a%20lawsuit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEffectively%20choosing%20judges%2C%20and%20knowing%20with%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20clarity%20how%20those%20judges%20would%20rule%2C%20was%20the%20very%20essence%20of%20the%20Jones%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee's%20motions%20seeking%20to%20disgorge%20nearly%20%2423%20million%20in%20fees%20Jackson%20Walker%20collected%20in%2033%20cases%20in%20front%20of%20Jones%20has%20been%20bottled%20up.%20Those%20cases%20have%20been%20combined%20into%20a%20single%20proceeding%2C%20overseen%20at%20this%20stage%20by%20Rodriguez.%20That%20consolidation%20delays%20or%20even%20prevents%20what%20many%20would%20like%3A%C2%A0an%20impartial%20judge%20from%20outside%20the%20district%20hearing%20the%20cases%20and%20putting%20key%20players%20in%20the%20machine%20under%20oath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Trustee%20began%20taking%20discovery%20on%20May%2015%2C%20according%20to%20a%20scheduling%20order%2C%20but%20a%20settlement%20could%20halt%20that%20process%20and%20eliminate%20the%20risk%20that%20Cavenaugh%2C%20Freeman%2C%20Jones%2C%20or%20even%20Isgur%20would%20have%20to%20testify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20be%20fine%20with%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bloomberglaw.com%2Fbankruptcy-law%2Fex-weil-partner-alfredo-perez-picked-as-houston-bankruptcy-judge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20circuit%20judges%20chose%20Alfredo%20Perez%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20retired%20Weil%2C%20Gotshal%20%26amp%3B%20Manges%20bankruptcy%20attorney%2C%20to%20replace%20Jones.%20The%20pick%20was%20widely%20interpreted%20as%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20had%20come%20to%20enjoy%20Houston's%20recent%20success%20and%20didn't%20want%20it%20to%20end%20with%20Jones'%20career.%20Isgur%20told%20Bloomberg%20recently%20that%20he%20plans%20to%20give%20up%20handling%20complex%20cases%2C%20which%20would%20clear%20the%20way%20for%20Perez%20to%20take%20over.%20Former%20chief%20Southern%20District%20judge%20Richard%20Schmidt%20told%20Bloomberg%20that%20Perez's%20experience%20handling%20large%20cases%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bgodsend%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20district.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20imagine%20a%20better%20selection%20given%20the%20circumstances%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20Debtwire%2C%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas'%20popularity%20has%20plunged.%20Through%20May%204%2C%20only%2010%25%20of%20the%20large%20Chapter%2011%20bankruptcy%20filings%20this%20year%20tracked%20by%20the%20data%20provider%20have%20been%20filed%20in%20the%20district%2C%20less%20than%20half%20what%20it%20was%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20well%20short%20of%20Delaware's%20current%20share%20%E2%80%94%C2%A039%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAdditional%20reporting%3A%20Jack%20Newsham.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconflicts-of-interest-deepen-southern-district-of-texas-bankruptcy-court-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717408322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665a3d65cc442a2f676cf0f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconflicts-of-interest-deepen-southern-district-of-texas-bankruptcy-court-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20details%20emerge%20about%20the%20tight-knit%20circle%20of%20attorneys%20and%20judges%20that%20fueled%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20nation's%20most%20influential%20bankruptcy%20court%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20spectacular%20fall.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dcampbell%2Bweb%40insider.com%20(Dakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconflicts-of-interest-deepen-southern-district-of-texas-bankruptcy-court-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SBI%20market%20cap%20crosses%20Rs%208%20lakh%20crore%3B%20stock%20hits%2052-week%20high%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717408132000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110663538%2Cimgsize-61126.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fsbi-market-capitalization-crosses-rs-8-lakh-crore-stock-hits-52-week-high-as-exit-polls-predict-modi-victory%2Farticleshow%2F110662693.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22State%20Bank%20of%20India's%20market%20capitalization%20surpassed%20Rs%208%20lakh%20crore%20as%20the%20stock%20hit%20a%2052-week%20high%20on%20exit%20polls%20predictions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fsbi-market-capitalization-crosses-rs-8-lakh-crore-stock-hits-52-week-high-as-exit-polls-predict-modi-victory%2Farticleshow%2F110662693.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Did%20Surat%20Election%20Violate%20Supreme%20Court's%20NOTA%20Verdict%3F%20Poll%20Body%20Replies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20can%20intervene%20if%20a%20candidate%20is%20pressured%20into%20withdrawing%20nomination%2C%20but%20not%20when%20it's%20consensual%2C%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20said%20today.%20He%20was%20replying%20to%20a%20question%20on%20the%20poll%20body's%20decision%20to%20announce%20BJP's%20Surat%20candidate%2C%20Mukesh%20Dalal%2C%20elected%20after%20the%20Congress%20pick's%20nomination%20was%20rejected%20and%20the%20other%20candidates%20withdrew%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP's%20Surat%20win%20had%20sparked%20a%20massive%20row%2C%20with%20the%20Congress%20alleging%20that%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%20used%20%26quot%3Bwrong%20and%20undue%20influence%26quot%3B%20and%20pressured%20candidates%20into%20withdrawing%20nominations.%20Many%20others%20had%20pointed%20that%20not%20polling%20in%20the%20constituency%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20voters'%20right%20as%20he%2Fshe%20could%20also%20opt%20for%20the%20NOTA%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20poll%20body's%20press%20meet%20ahead%20of%20counting%20day%2C%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20was%20asked%20if%20its%20decision%20to%20declare%20a%20candidate%20elected%20unopposed%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%202013%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20on%20the%20NOTA%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20democracy%20to%20survive%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20the%20best%20available%20men%20should%20be%20chosen%20as%20people's%20representatives%20for%20proper%20governance%20of%20the%20country.%20This%20can%20be%20best%20achieved%20through%20men%20of%20high%20moral%20and%20ethical%20values%2C%20who%20win%20the%20elections%20on%20a%20positive%20vote.%20Thus%20in%20a%20vibrant%20democracy%2C%20the%20voter%20must%20be%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20choose%C2%A0none%20of%20the%20above%20(NOTA)%20button%2C%20which%20will%20indeed%20compel%20the%20political%20parties%20to%20nominate%20a%20sound%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20said%20in%20the%20landmark%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20poll%20officer%20was%20also%20asked%20if%20the%20Election%20Commission%20will%20consider%20an%20amendment%20in%20rules%20so%20that%20no%20candidate%20is%20declared%20unopposed%20and%20people%20have%20an%20option%20to%20vote%20for%20NOTA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20Mr%20Kumar%20said%20the%20poll%20body%20wants%20contests%20on%20every%20seat.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20candidates%20decide%20to%20withdraw%20nominations%2C%20what%20can%20we%20do%3F%20If%20they%20are%20under%20pressure%2C%20if%20they%20are%20locked%20up%20or%20forced%2C%20that's%20where%20our%20role%20comes%20in.%20But%20if%20they%20are%20doing%20it%20of%20their%20own%20will%2C%20how%20would%20I...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTherefore%2C%20if%20you%20want%20a%20law%20according%20to%20which%20there%20will%20be%20no%20election%20where%20there%20is%20only%20candidate%2C%20I%20do%20not%20think%20that%20would%20be%20right.%20But%20it%20is%20a%20must%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20one%20is%20forcefully%20removed%20as%20a%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20media%20this%20afternoon%2C%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20rejected%20the%20Congress%20leader%20Jairam%20Ramesh's%20allegations%20that%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20called%20up%20district%20magistrates%20after%20voting%20and%20accused%20the%20BJP%20of%20%26quot%3Bblatant%20and%20brazen%20intimidation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrashing%20the%20charge%2C%20Mr%20Kumar%20said%20it%20is%20not%20right%20to%20spread%20%26quot%3Brumour%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdoubt%20everyone%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCan%20someone%20influence%20them%20all%3F%20(district%20magistrates%2Freturning%20officers)%20all%3F%20Can%20anyone%20influence%20500-600%20people%3F%20Tell%20us%20who%20did%20this.%20We%20will%20punish%20the%20person%20who%20did%20it.%20They%20should%20tell%20the%20details%20before%20counting%20the%20votes.%20It%20is%20not%20right%20that%20you%20spread%20a%20rumour%20and%20doubt%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717408080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F3hvnvefo_election-commission_625x300_03_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felection-commission-of-india-surat-lok-sabha-seat-2024-lok-sabha-election-did-surat-election-violate-supreme-courts-nota-verdict-poll-body-replies-5806389%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Election%20Commission%20can%20intervene%20if%20a%20candidate%20is%20pressured%20into%20withdrawing%20nomination